Full pom.xml Configuration

The pom.xml file is set to run Python tests using xmlrunner and exec-maven-plugin, ensuring the virtual environment is used correctly by pointing explicitly to the virtual environment’s Python interpreter.

<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/maven-v4_0_0.xsd">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
    
    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>plainid-management-automation</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

    <build>
        <plugins>
            <!-- Exec Maven Plugin to run Python tests with xmlrunner -->
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.codehaus.mojo</groupId>
                <artifactId>exec-maven-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.0.0</version>
                <executions>
                    <execution>
                        <phase>test</phase>
                        <goals>
                            <goal>exec</goal>
                        </goals>
                        <configuration>
                            <!-- Explicitly using Python from virtual environment -->
                            <executable>${project.basedir}/venv/bin/python</executable>
                            <arguments>
                                <argument>-m</argument>
                                <argument>xmlrunner</argument>
                                <argument>discover</argument>
                                <argument>-s</argument>
                                <argument>unittests</argument>
                                <argument>-p</argument>
                                <argument>*.py</argument>
                                <argument>-o</argument>
                                <argument>reports/</argument>
                            </arguments>
                        </configuration>
                    </execution>
                </executions>
            </plugin>

            <!-- Optionally, skip Java tests using Surefire Plugin if not needed -->
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>2.22.2</version>
                <configuration>
                    <skipTests>true</skipTests>
                </configuration>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>
</project>

Key Points:

exec-maven-plugin is configured to explicitly call the python executable from the virtual environment (${project.basedir}/venv/bin/python).

Python tests are run with xmlrunner, and the results are output to the reports/ directory.

Surefire Plugin is optionally set to skip Java tests if you're not running any Java tests and only using Python tests.



