Full Jenkinsfile Configuration

This Jenkinsfile ensures that the Python virtual environment is properly set up and activated. It also ensures that the Python tests are executed using the virtual environment's Python interpreter.

pipeline {
    agent { label 'linux && region-eu && jdk-17-zulu && python-3.11' }

    environment {
        PYTHON_ENV = 'venv/bin/python'
        VENV_DIR = 'venv'
        REQUIREMENTS_PATH = 'resources/requirements.txt'
        REPORTS_DIR = 'reports'
    }

    stages {
        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                cleanWs() // Clean workspace before starting
                checkout scm // Checkout the repository code
            }
        }

        stage('Setup Python Environment') {
            steps {
                script {
                    sh """
                    echo "Setting up Python Virtual Environment"
                    python3.11 -m venv ${VENV_DIR}
                    source ${VENV_DIR}/bin/activate

                    # Ensure we are using the correct Python
                    echo "Using Python interpreter: $(which python)"
                    pip install --upgrade pip
                    pip install requests-mock unittest-xml-reporting

                    echo "Installed packages:"
                    pip freeze
                    """
                }
            }
        }

        stage('Run Python Unittests') {
            steps {
                script {
                    sh """
                    echo "Running Python tests using xmlrunner..."
                    mkdir -p ${REPORTS_DIR}
                    ${VENV_DIR}/bin/python -m xmlrunner discover -s unittests -p "*.py" -o ${REPORTS_DIR}/

                    echo "Listing contents of ${REPORTS_DIR}:"
                    ls -al ${REPORTS_DIR}
                    """
                }
            }
        }

        stage('Run Maven Build') {
            steps {
                script {
                    sh """
                    echo "Running Maven build..."
                    mvn clean test
                    """
                }
            }
        }
    }

    post {
        always {
            archiveArtifacts artifacts: '**/target/*.jar', allowEmptyArchive: true
            junit 'reports/TESTS-TestSuite.xml'
        }
    }
}

Key Points:

The virtual environment is explicitly created and activated using python3.11 -m venv venv, and the pip install commands ensure the necessary packages (unittest-xml-reporting and requests-mock) are installed.

The Python tests are run using the explicit path to the Python binary inside the virtual environment (${VENV_DIR}/bin/python).

A Maven build is triggered with mvn clean test to run the Python tests as part of the Maven build process.



